pack of cards;—it is not these things alone which make tearless Lima, the 
strangest, saddest city thou can’st see. For Lima has taken the white veil; 
and there is a higher horror in this whiteness of her woe. Old as Pizarro, this 
whiteness keeps her ruins for ever new; admits not the cheerful greenness of 
